  <article class="container-prose prose-editorial cs-body" set:html={`<h3><b>Educational Case Study Disclosure</b></h3><p>This case study is hypothetical and for educational purposes only. Scenarios, borrower profiles, loan terms, interest rates, and outcomes are illustrative examples and do not represent current offers or guaranteed terms.</p><p>For specific details including down payment requirements, closing cost estimates, interest rate details, closing cost breakdowns, payment calculations, cash-to-close estimates, or an official Loan Estimate, it is highly recommended you<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a meeting with one of our licensed mortgage advisors</a>.</p><p><b>Learn more:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/24/">Resort condo loan purchase Reg Z advertising requirements (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB official regulation</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1026">Resort condo loan purchase Reg Z full text and compliance</a> – Electronic Code of Federal Regulations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/interp-24/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Official resort condo loan purchase advertising interpretations (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB interpretations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1014" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Resort condo loan purchase MAP Rule (Reg N) mortgage advertising</a> – Mortgage advertising rules</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/">NMLS Consumer Access – Verify resort condo loan purchase lender licensure</a></li></ul><p>Actual loan terms vary by credit profile, property, occupancy, location, market conditions, and lender guidelines. For current options tailored to you,<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a consultation</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> apply online</a>.</p><p>Ready to explore your options?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor.</p>		
					<h2>Discover How a Resort Condo Loan Made This Non-Warrantable Property Purchase Possible</h2>				
		<p>Katherine B., a 47-year-old corporate executive based in Atlanta, Georgia, had built substantial wealth through her successful technology career. She earned a strong six-figure income, maintained excellent credit, and owned her primary residence free and clear after years of accelerated payments. Katherine was ready to diversify her investment portfolio by purchasing a luxury beachfront condominium in Destin, Florida—a property she could enjoy personally while generating rental income when she wasn't using it.</p><p>Katherine identified the perfect two-bedroom, two-bathroom unit with Gulf views in a desirable resort condominium complex featuring hotel-style amenities, on-site rental management, and strong occupancy rates. The property represented everything she wanted: personal vacation enjoyment, rental income potential, long-term appreciation in a premiere beach market, and eventually, a retirement home. This wasn't just about buying one vacation property; it was about building a diversified real estate portfolio that would create passive income streams and provide lifestyle flexibility as she approached retirement while establishing a valuable asset for her family's future.</p><p>Facing similar challenges?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to explore your options.</p><h2><b>The Challenge: Why Traditional Lenders Rejected the Resort Condo</b></h2><p>Katherine approached three traditional mortgage lenders, confident her strong financial profile would make approval straightforward. She had excellent credit, substantial income, significant liquid reserves, and no existing debt. Each lender reviewed the property details and delivered the same disappointing response: the condominium was "non-warrantable," making it ineligible for conventional financing through their programs.</p><h3><b>Why Did Traditional Lenders Reject Katherine's Resort Condo Loan Request?</b></h3><p>Traditional mortgage lenders require condominiums to meet strict "warrantability" criteria established by Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac before they'll provide conventional financing. Katherine's chosen resort condominium failed several of these requirements: the complex had an on-site hotel-style rental program managed by the developer, more than a specified percentage of units were rented short-term rather than owner-occupied, the Homeowners Association derived substantial income from commercial amenities, and individual unit owners couldn't opt out of the mandatory rental program.</p><h3><b>How Do Resort Condo Loans Differ from Traditional Condo Financing?</b></h3><p>"The property was absolutely beautiful—Gulf-front views, excellent condition, strong rental history, and professionally managed," Katherine explained. "But traditional lenders said the rental program structure made it non-warrantable. They explained that Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac won't purchase loans on condos with certain rental program characteristics, so they couldn't offer conventional financing regardless of my financial strength."</p><h3><b>What Makes Resort Condominiums Non-Warrantable?</b></h3><p>Katherine's real estate agent had actually warned her that many premiere resort condominiums face financing challenges due to their structure. Resort condos often feature characteristics that conventional lenders avoid: mandatory rental programs, hotel-style amenities and services, low owner-occupancy ratios, commercial space within the complex, or single-entity ownership of multiple units. These features create attractive investment properties with strong rental potential but make them ineligible for conventional financing.</p><h3><b>What Alternative Properties Did Katherine Consider?</b></h3><p>One lender suggested Katherine consider a different condominium complex with higher owner-occupancy and no rental program—essentially asking her to compromise on the investment characteristics that made the property attractive. Another suggested she pay cash, eliminating the financing challenge entirely but tying up substantial liquid capital she preferred to keep invested and diversified.</p><p>"I didn't want to compromise on the property or tie up excessive capital in a single asset," Katherine said. "This specific unit in this specific complex offered exactly what I wanted—strong rental income potential when I wasn't using it, professional management, and premiere beach location. I needed a lender who could finance resort condominiums despite their non-warrantable status."</p><p>Experiencing similar rejection?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to discuss alternative qualification methods.</p><h2><b>The Discovery: How Katherine Found Resort Condo Loan Programs</b></h2><p>Katherine discovered resort condo loan programs through her real estate agent, who specialized in resort property sales and had connections with lenders focusing on non-warrantable condominium financing. The agent explained that specialized resort condo lenders understand these properties' unique characteristics and structure loans specifically for condominiums that conventional lenders won't finance.</p><h3><b>What Makes Resort Condo Loans Different from Traditional Condo Mortgages?</b></h3><p>During her consultation with a resort condo loan specialist, Katherine learned how these programs are specifically designed for condominiums in resort areas that don't meet conventional warrantability standards. Resort condo lenders evaluate properties based on location quality, property condition, rental performance history, and borrower financial strength—rather than rigid warrantability checklists that disqualify most resort properties.</p><p>The loan advisor explained that resort condo lenders assess several critical factors: borrower financial strength and reserves, property location and market demand, historical rental performance and occupancy rates, property condition and maintenance standards, and Homeowners Association financial health. Unlike conventional lenders who automatically reject non-warrantable condos, resort condo lenders understand that mandatory rental programs and hotel-style amenities often indicate well-managed, income-producing properties that perform excellently for both lenders and borrowers.</p><h3><b>How Did Katherine Qualify for a Resort Condo Loan?</b></h3><p>"That conversation was incredibly reassuring," Katherine explained. "The lender reviewed my financial profile—excellent credit, strong income, substantial reserves—and discussed the property's rental history, occupancy rates, and market demand. They understood that the rental program wasn't a negative; it was actually a positive feature that would generate income and provide professional management. They evaluated the complete picture rather than automatically disqualifying the property based on warrantability criteria."</p><p>The resort condo loan specialist understood that Katherine represented an ideal borrower profile: established professional with strong income, excellent credit history, substantial liquid reserves, and clear investment strategy. The property represented an excellent collateral position in a premiere beach market with proven rental demand. This wasn't just solving a warrantability problem—it was enabling a sophisticated investor to acquire a high-quality asset that would provide both personal enjoyment and investment returns while diversifying her portfolio.</p><h2><b>The Solution: Resort Condo Loan Approval Process</b></h2><p>Katherine worked with her loan advisor to assemble documentation for her resort condo loan application. The process focused on demonstrating her financial strength, the property's quality and rental performance, and the overall investment viability.</p><h3><b>What Documentation Did Katherine Provide for Resort Condo Loan Approval?</b></h3><p><b>Documentation provided:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Recent pay stubs and employment verification letter</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Two years of personal tax returns</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Bank and investment account statements showing substantial reserves</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Credit report demonstrating excellent payment history</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Current primary residence property information (owned free and clear)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Detailed property information including rental history and occupancy rates</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Homeowners Association financial statements and budget</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Property appraisal ordered by lender</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Rental program agreement and management company information</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Property inspection report showing excellent condition</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Proof of adequate down payment funds and reserves</li></ul><h3><b>How Long Does Resort Condo Loan Approval Take?</b></h3><p><b>The approval process:</b></p><ol><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Initial consultation</b> - Discussed property type and non-warrantable status</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Borrower financial review</b> - Evaluated credit, income, and reserves</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Property evaluation</b> - Analyzed location, condition, and rental performance</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>HOA review</b> - Examined association financial health and management</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Appraisal ordered</b> - Property appraised at purchase price</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Rental program analysis</b> - Reviewed management agreement and income projections</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Conditional approval</b> - Approved pending final documentation</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Clear to close</b> - Final approval issued</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Closing</b> - Funded and closed in under six weeks from application</li></ol><p>The resort condo lender structured the loan with terms appropriate for non-warrantable resort condominiums. The down payment requirement was higher than conventional financing but manageable given Katherine's substantial reserves. The interest rate reflected the property type and non-warrantable status while remaining competitive for investment property financing. The loan maintained a standard long-term fixed-rate structure, providing predictable payments and long-term wealth-building potential.</p><p>Ready to purchase?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/purchase-inquiry/"> Submit a purchase inquiry</a> to discuss your scenario.</p><h2><b>The Results: Katherine Acquires Premiere Resort Property</b></h2><p>Katherine closed on her resort condominium in under six weeks after submitting her application. The two-bedroom, two-bathroom Gulf-front unit in Destin, Florida provided everything she envisioned—stunning views, luxury finishes, hotel-style amenities, and immediate enrollment in the professional rental management program.</p><h3><b>What Results Did Katherine Achieve with Resort Condo Loan Financing?</b></h3><p><b>Final loan outcome:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Approved loan amount covered purchase with appropriate down payment for resort property</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Competitive interest rate for non-warrantable resort condo financing</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Standard long-term fixed-rate mortgage structure</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Appropriate down payment preserved substantial liquid reserves for other investments</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Timeline: Application to closing in under six weeks</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Property: 2BR/2BA Gulf-front condo, Destin, FL</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Rental program: Enrolled immediately with professional management</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Monthly rental income: Generating positive cash flow when not personally occupied</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Personal use: Available for family vacations and weekend getaways</li></ul><h3><b>How Did Resort Condo Loan Compare to Alternative Financing Options?</b></h3><p><b>Conventional financing vs. resort condo loan:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Conventional availability:</b> Not available due to non-warrantable status</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Resort condo loan availability:</b> Specifically designed for non-warrantable properties</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Cash purchase alternative:</b> Would have tied up excessive liquid capital</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Resort condo loan advantage:</b> Preserved capital for diversification and reserves</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Investment property goal:</b> ACHIEVED ✓</li></ul><p><b>Property compromise vs. preferred resort condo:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Warrantable condo alternative:</b> Available but without rental program and amenities</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Chosen resort condo:</b> Mandatory rental program generating strong income</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Warrantable location:</b> Less desirable location and rental potential</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Resort location:</b> Premiere beach market with excellent appreciation history</li></ul><p>Katherine's resort condominium generates attractive rental income during peak season and shoulder periods when she's not using it personally. The professional management company handles all bookings, guest services, maintenance, and accounting—providing truly passive income. Katherine blocks the property for her own use during her preferred vacation periods, enjoying a luxury beachfront retreat without the full ownership costs of a second home used only occasionally.</p><h3><b>What Would Have Happened Without Resort Condo Loan Access?</b></h3><p>"Without the resort condo loan program, I would have either paid cash and tied up excessive capital in one asset, or compromised on the property and purchased a less desirable warrantable condo without the rental program features I wanted," Katherine explained. "The resort condo loan let me acquire exactly the property I wanted while maintaining a diversified investment portfolio. Now I'm generating rental income, enjoying personal vacation use, and building equity in a premiere beach market."</p><p>Katherine's monthly payment is comfortably covered by rental income during occupied periods, and her substantial reserves easily handle expenses during gaps or personal use periods. The tax benefits of investment property ownership—including mortgage interest deductions, depreciation, and expense deductions—provide additional financial advantages. The property has already appreciated since purchase, building equity while generating income.</p><p>"This isn't just about owning one vacation property," Katherine added. "It's about building a diversified real estate portfolio across different property types and markets. The resort condo provides personal lifestyle benefits, generates passive income, and diversifies my holdings beyond stocks and my primary residence. As I approach retirement, I'm already planning to purchase additional resort properties in different destinations—perhaps ski properties in Colorado and golf resort condos in Arizona."</p><p>When Katherine is ready to purchase additional resort properties, she'll use the same resort condo loan strategy to acquire properties that conventional lenders won't finance. She's also considering eventually using a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/heloc"> HELOC</a> on her debt-free primary residence to fund down payments on future resort properties, or exploring<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/dscr-loans"> DSCR loans</a> for traditional rental properties to further diversify her real estate holdings. The resort condo proved that non-warrantable properties can be excellent investments when financed properly.</p><p>Ready to get started?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> Get approved</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a call</a> to discuss your situation.</p><h2><b>Exploring Other Resort Condo Loan Options?</b></h2><p>While Katherine used a resort condo loan to purchase a beachfront investment property, resort condo loan financing works for multiple scenarios:</p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Need investment property financing? See how an<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/dscr-loan-purchase"> investor used DSCR loans for rental properties</a></li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Want vacation home financing? See how a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/second-home-loan-purchase"> professional used second home loans for personal retreats</a></li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> to find success stories matching your situation</li></ul><h2><b>Key Takeaways for Resort Condo Investors</b></h2><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Resort condo loans finance non-warrantable properties rejected by conventional lenders—specifically designed for condominiums in resort areas with rental programs, hotel-style amenities, or other characteristics that fail Fannie Mae/Freddie Mac warrantability requirements</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Mandatory rental programs create passive income opportunities—professionally managed rental programs generate attractive returns while providing personal use flexibility when owners want vacation enjoyment (<a href="https://www.fanniemae.com/">Fannie Mae condo project standards</a>)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Strong borrower profiles strengthen applications significantly—excellent credit, substantial reserves, and clear investment strategies demonstrate capability to handle resort property ownership successfully</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Premiere resort locations justify higher down payments—desirable beach, ski, and golf resort markets with proven rental demand and appreciation potential represent excellent long-term investments</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Think beyond the single transaction</b>—successful investors build diversified real estate portfolios across multiple property types and resort destinations, using resort condo loans to acquire properties that provide both lifestyle benefits and investment returns, creating wealth through strategic vacation property ownership that conventional financing can't accommodate</li></ul><p>Have questions about qualifying with resort condo loan programs?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor today.</p><h2><b>Alternative Loan Programs for Resort and Vacation Property Investors</b></h2><p>If a resort condo loan isn't the perfect fit, consider these alternatives:</p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/second-home-loans">Second Home Loan</a> – Financing for vacation homes with personal use focus</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/dscr-loans">DSCR Loan</a> – Investment property financing based on rental income</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/portfolio-loans">Portfolio Loan</a> – Flexible underwriting for unique properties</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/bank-statement-loans">Bank Statement Loan</a> – Alternative documentation for self-employed borrowers</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/asset-based-loans">Asset-Based Loan</a> – Qualify based on investment portfolios and liquid assets</li></ul><p><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/">Explore all loan programs</a> to find your best option.</p><h2><b>Helpful Resort Condo Loan Purchase Resources</b></h2><p><b>Learn more about this loan program:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/resort-condo-loans">Complete Resort Condo Loan Guide</a> - Detailed requirements, rates, and qualification guidelines</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculator/resort-condo-calculator">Resort Condo Loan Calculator</a> - Estimate your qualification</li></ul><p><b>Similar success stories:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/dscr-loan-purchase">How an investor used DSCR loans for traditional rental properties</a> - No income verification strategy</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/second-home-loan-purchase">Professional purchases second home with vacation financing</a> - Personal use focus</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> - Browse by your journey stage</li></ul><p><b>External authoritative resources:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.fanniemae.com/">Fannie Mae condo project eligibility standards</a> - Understanding warrantability requirements</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://www.nar.realtor/">National Association of Realtors - Vacation home market data</a> - Resort property investment insights</li></ul><p><b>Ready to get started?</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/">Apply online</a> - Start your application today</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/">Schedule a consultation</a> - Discuss your specific situation</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/discovery-quiz/">Take the discovery quiz</a> - Clarify your goals</li></ul><p>Need local expertise?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/get-a-local-introduction/"> Get introduced to trusted partners</a> including loan officers, realtors, and contractors in your area.</p><p> </p>		
